This is a small breeding colony of black-headed gulls.  From time-to-time they mobbed a little egret when it went too close to the nests (here is some video taken at about the same time, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xL-KnsjUOck - the mobbing is toward the end).  Some of the gulls were clearly courtship displaying (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JuS4-4q_Iek) and, I think, nesting was in fairly early stages.  The location is a scrape on a nature reserve run by Essex Wildlife Trust.  There were also two oystercatchers here that, I think, can be heard in the recording occasionally.
